OL,3,C'I have to see my dad's killer in
OL,4,CTesco' - son of man killed in one-
OL,5,Cpunch attack
OL,7,FDespite Elmes' lies, Mr Minshull was
OL,8,Facquitted.
OL,10,FAfter the acquittal, Adam says Elmes
OL,11,Fbought him a pint to try to console
OL,12,Fhim about the trial's result.
OL,14,F"Unbeknownst to us, it was actually
OL,15,Fhim who had killed our dad. We've had
OL,16,F15 years of that moment of deceit,
OL,17,Fit's played on my mind for years and
OL,18,Fyears and years. This is probably the
OL,19,Ffirst time I've ever spoken about that
OL,20,Fmoment."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/7
